  <revision rev="3" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>3dce96cc6311e9df24ef92a46c7ca193</srcmd5>
    <version>0.32.0</version>
    <time>1768336008</time>
    <user>anag_factory</user>
    <comment>- Fix CVEs
  * GO-2025-4135 (CVE-2025-47914)
    SSH Agent servers do not validate the size of messages
    when processing new identity requests, which may cause
    the program to panic if the message is malformed due to
    an out of bounds read.
  * GO-2025-4116 (CVE-2025-47913)
    SSH clients receiving SSH_AGENT_SUCCESS when expecting a
    typed response will panic and cause early termination of
    the client process.
  * GO-2025-4134 (CVE-2025-58181, bsc#1253952).
    SSH servers parsing GSSAPI authentication
    requests do not validate the number of mechanisms
    specified in the request, allowing an attacker to cause
    unbounded memory consumption.

- Update to 0.32.0
  Feat: Add option to require approval before tool.
  Bump github.com/cloudwego/eino to fix panic.
  Changes to 0.31.4:
  Update dependencies.
  Changes to 0.31.3:
  Fix format &amp; update models.
  Changes to 0.31.2:
  Fix: suppress health check logging to debug output only/
  Changes to 0.31.1:
  Update dependency update mcp-go.

- Add shell completions &amp; basic %check during build time.</comment>
    <requestid>1326790</requestid>
  </revision>
  <revision rev="4" vrev="1">
    <srcmd5>22eab200b9302bb25afd3f4e5b83790a</srcmd5>
    <version>0.34.0</version>
    <time>1778263716</time>
    <user>dimstar_suse</user>
    <comment>- Updated to version 0.34.0
  * Features:
    - Upgraded charmbracelet libs to v2 (bubbletea, lipgloss, bubbles)
    - Added Google Vertex AI support for Claude models
    - Added new models.
  * Fix:
    - Eliminated escape sequence leak from spinner tea.Program instances.
    - Fix anthropic api issue.
    - Converted JSON Schema draft-07 exclusive bounds to draft-04 format.
  * Upgraded all dependencies to latest versions, resolve security issues
    and for Go 1.26 compatibility.
    This addressed CVE-2025-30153 GO-2025-3533.
- Fixed CVEs:
  * CVE-2026-33186 GO-2026-4762 (bsc#1260224)
  * CVE-2026-32285 GO-2026-4514 (bsc#1261230)</comment>
